                              <td width="10%" bgcolor="white" valign="top" align="center" rowspan="3"><img src="/cms/deliver.html?id=announcement.gif" alt="Announcement"></td>
                              <td width="90%" colspan="2" bgcolor="#5B96D8"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;">REDBRICK UPDATE: 2004-03-08 (James Flowers) -
                                    2004-03-16 -
                                    03:41:31</font></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr bgcolor="#7EB4FA">
                              <td colspan="2"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 11px;">Hi all, just a quick update in case you think things have been quiet here at RedBrick (if you've been reading other ED forums,
                                    you will know it hasn't *grin*). We're moving along with a number of products. In particular, the Compendiums are getting
                                    a thorough workover at present, on their way to getting them to Playtest status. Thanks for your all your patience to date.
                                    Hard to believe that 4 months has gone by, but it has! To answer the obvious question? No firm ETA for books at this stage,
                                    but we're making good progress, and our original plan is still running on schedule. Be assured that once we get firm release
                                    dates, you'll read it here first. Take kaer, JAMES FLOWERS (Line Developer, RedBrick Limited)</font></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr bgcolor="#7EB4FA">
                              <td align="left" width="40%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 9px;"><a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com:80/readMore.html?id=1550">Read More...</a></font></td>
                              <td align="right" width="60%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 9px;" size="-1">0 messages in 0 threads.</font><br><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 9px;" size="-1">Last comment on 16/03/04</font><br></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td width="10%" bgcolor="white" valign="top" align="center" rowspan="3"><img src="/cms/deliver.html?id=announcement.gif" alt="Announcement"></td>
                              <td width="90%" colspan="2" bgcolor="#5B96D8"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;">Book Of Tomorrow now taking articles for Issue 5 (Richard Vowles) -
                                    2004-02-19 -
                                    07:28:38</font></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr bgcolor="#A0D5FF">
                              <td colspan="2"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 11px;">The EDPT would like to officially announce that they
                                    are taking article submissions for Book of Tomorrow
                                    issue 5. The deadline for first drafts is May 31,
                                    2004. As usual, the EDPT is having a contest for the
                                    best article, but for BoT5, the prize is a little
                                    different -- instead of a copy of an in-print
                                    Earthdawn book, they are offering a limited edition
                                    hardcover Earthdawn rulebook (the 'red book'),
                                    numbered 234 out of 1000. More information can be
                                    found in BoT4, and they'll be putting together a more
                                    comprehensive announcement soon, to be posted on the
                                    edpt-l, earthdawn and earthdawn-gm mailing lists, as
                                    well as several forums, including <a href="http://earthdawn.whitegriffin.com" target="_blank">EDPT's own forum</a>, and WERG.</font></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr bgcolor="#A0D5FF">
                              <td align="left" width="40%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 9px;"><a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com:80/readMore.html?id=1438">Read More...</a></font></td>
                              <td align="right" width="60%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 9px;" size="-1">0 messages in 0 threads.</font><br><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 9px;" size="-1">Last comment on 19/02/04</font><br></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td width="10%" bgcolor="#7EB4FA" valign="top" align="center" rowspan="3"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px">General</font></td>
                              <td width="90%" colspan="2" bgcolor="#5B96D8"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;">Nightmares of mine... (Richard Vowles) -
                                    2004-02-09 -
                                    00:42:50</font></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr bgcolor="#7EB4FA">
                              <td colspan="2"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" style="font-size: 11px;">I came across this book as a recommendation from those who run Horror oriented games and purchased it on eBay - it is out
                                    of print by I.C.E still sell it. It is really the very best "how to" roleplaying book that I have read - it covers all of
                                    the details you would need to know about how to write and run an excellent horror based scenario. It has no game specifics
                                    in it, and mentions are a wide range of different roleplaying games. If you are interested in it, it can be picked up from
                                    I.C.E's store at <a href="http://store.ironcrown.com/detail.jsp?itemId=2023&amp;category=10099" target="_blank">this location.</a></font></td>
                           </tr>
